    slug: "upload-photos",
    category: "GETTING_STARTED",
    summary: "Upload photos using drag-and-drop, file browser, or the mobile app. Fotiqo supports batch uploads of hundreds of photos at once.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Open the gallery you want to add photos to from the Galleries page.\n2. Click the Upload button or drag files directly onto the gallery area.\n3. Select one or multiple photos from your computer using the file browser.\n4. Monitor the upload progress bar for each file.\n5. Once uploaded, photos are automatically processed and thumbnails are generated.\n6. Reorder photos by dragging them to the desired position.\n7. Click Save to confirm the photo arrangement.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** For fastest uploads, resize your photos to web-optimized JPGs before uploading. You can keep originals stored locally as backup.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: What is the maximum file size per photo?**\nA: Each photo can be up to 100 MB. For RAW files, the limit is 200 MB.\n\n**Q: Can I upload from my phone?**\nA: Yes, use the Fotiqo mobile app to upload directly from your phone camera roll.\n\n**Q: Do uploads continue if I close the browser?**\nA: Uploads pause if you close the browser. Keep the tab open until all uploads complete.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to create your first gallery step by step](/help/first-gallery-step-by-step)\n- [How to set up watermarks on your galleries](/help/setup-watermarks)\n- [How to use the Fotiqo mobile app](/help/install-mobile-app)",
