    summary: "Enable your store to sell prints, wall art, albums, and digital downloads. Set pricing, connect fulfillment, and start earning.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Store in the left sidebar and click Enable Store.\n2. Browse the product catalog and select which products you want to offer.\n3. Set your markup pricing for each product size and type.\n4. Upload sample images to preview how your products will look.\n5. Configure shipping options and delivery zones.\n6. Connect your Stripe account for payment processing.\n7. Test the store by placing a sample order.\n8. Enable the store on your galleries so clients can purchase prints.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Start with a few popular products like 8x10 prints and 16x20 canvas wraps. You can always add more products later.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Who handles printing and shipping?**\nA: Fotiqo partners with professional print labs who handle printing, packaging, and shipping directly to your client.\n\n**Q: How do I set my prices?**\nA: You set a markup on top of the base cost. Your profit is the difference between your selling price and the base cost.\n\n**Q: Can clients order from any gallery?**\nA: Only galleries with the store enabled will show purchase options to clients.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to set product pricing and markups](/help/price-sheets)\n- [How to manage store orders](/help/managing-orders)\n- [How to connect your Stripe account for payments](/help/setup-payments)",
