    slug: "create-contracts",
    category: "GETTING_STARTED",
    summary: "Create professional photography contracts using templates or from scratch. Send contracts for e-signature and track signing status.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Navigate to Contracts in the left sidebar.\n2. Click New Contract and choose from a template or start blank.\n3. Fill in the contract details including client name, session date, and deliverables.\n4. Add your terms and conditions, cancellation policy, and payment terms.\n5. Insert signature fields where the client needs to sign.\n6. Preview the contract to make sure everything looks correct.\n7. Click Send to Client and enter their email address.\n8. Track the contract status from your Contracts dashboard.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Save your most-used contract as a template so you can create new contracts in seconds for future clients.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Are e-signatures legally binding?**\nA: Yes, Fotiqo e-signatures comply with e-signature laws and are legally binding in most jurisdictions.\n\n**Q: Can I edit a contract after sending it?**\nA: You can void a sent contract and create a new version if changes are needed.\n\n**Q: Will I be notified when a client signs?**\nA: Yes, you receive an email notification immediately when a client signs your contract.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to use contract templates](/help/contract-templates)\n- [How to create and send invoices](/help/create-invoice)\n- [How to track payments and send reminders](/help/payment-tracking)",
