    summary: "Generate professional invoices for your photography services. Send them to clients and track payment status automatically.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Invoices in the left sidebar and click New Invoice.\n2. Select the client from your contacts or enter their details manually.\n3. Add line items for each service such as session fee, prints, or album.\n4. Set the due date and any applicable tax rates.\n5. Add your payment terms and any notes for the client.\n6. Preview the invoice to check all details are correct.\n7. Click Send Invoice to email it to your client.\n8. The client can pay directly through the invoice link via Stripe.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Set up automatic payment reminders so you never have to chase late payments manually.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Can I send partial invoices or deposits?**\nA: Yes, you can create invoices for deposit amounts and send a final invoice for the remaining balance.\n\n**Q: What payment methods can clients use?**\nA: Clients can pay via credit card, debit card, or bank transfer through Stripe.\n\n**Q: Can I customize the invoice design?**\nA: Yes, you can add your logo and customize the color scheme of your invoices.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to create contracts and send them to clients](/help/create-contracts)\n- [How to connect your Stripe account for payments](/help/setup-payments)\n- [How to track payments and send reminders](/help/payment-tracking)",
