    summary: "Connect Stripe to accept credit card payments from clients. Receive payouts directly to your bank account.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Settings > Payments in your dashboard.\n2. Click Connect with Stripe to begin the setup.\n3. Create a new Stripe account or sign in to your existing one.\n4. Enter your business details including business type and address.\n5. Add your bank account information for receiving payouts.\n6. Verify your identity by uploading the required documents.\n7. Once approved, Stripe will be connected and ready to accept payments.\n8. Test the connection by processing a small test payment.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Stripe approval usually takes less than 24 hours. You can start setting up galleries and your store while you wait.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: What currencies does Stripe support?**\nA: Stripe supports over 135 currencies. Your account currency is set during Stripe onboarding.\n\n**Q: When do I receive my payouts?**\nA: Standard payouts arrive in your bank account 2 to 7 business days after a sale, depending on your country.\n\n**Q: Are there any fees?**\nA: Stripe charges standard processing fees per transaction. Fotiqo adds a small commission on sales.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How Fotiqo pricing and commission works](/help/commission-explained)\n- [How to understand your revenue dashboard](/help/revenue-dashboard)\n- [How to create and send invoices](/help/create-invoices)",
