    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Open your website page where you want the contact form.\n2. Add a Contact Form block from the block editor.\n3. Customize the form fields: name, email, phone, message, and session type.\n4. Add optional fields like preferred date, location, and budget.\n5. Set the email address where submissions should be sent.\n6. Configure an auto-reply message that clients receive after submitting.\n7. Customize the submit button text and success message.\n8. Save and publish the page.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Keep your contact form short. Name, email, and message are essential. Every extra field reduces the submission rate.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Can I receive form submissions on my phone?**\nA: Yes, enable push notifications in the mobile app to receive alerts for new form submissions.\n\n**Q: Is there spam protection?**\nA: Yes, contact forms include invisible CAPTCHA protection to prevent spam submissions.\n\n**Q: Can I export form submissions?**\nA: Yes, export all submissions as a CSV from the Website > Leads section.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to build your photography website](/help/build-website)\n- [How to use the block editor to build pages](/help/website-block-editor)\n- [How to configure SEO settings for your website](/help/seo-settings)",
