    summary: "Send contracts to clients for electronic signature. Track signing status and receive notifications when contracts are signed.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Open the contract you want to send.\n2. Verify all details are correct and signature fields are placed.\n3. Click Send for Signature.\n4. Enter the client email address.\n5. Add an optional personal message that accompanies the contract email.\n6. Choose whether to require your signature as well.\n7. Click Send and the client receives an email with a link to sign.\n8. Track the status from your Contracts dashboard: Sent, Viewed, Signed.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Send contracts early in the booking process. Signed contracts protect both you and the client.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Can I send to multiple signers?**\nA: Yes, add multiple signer email addresses if the contract requires signatures from more than one party.\n\n**Q: What if the client does not have access to email?**\nA: You can share the signing link directly via WhatsApp or any messaging platform.\n\n**Q: Can clients sign on their phone?**\nA: Yes, the signing experience is fully mobile-friendly.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to create a photography contract](/help/create-contract)\n- [How the client signing experience works](/help/client-signing)\n- [How to create and send invoices](/help/create-invoice)",
    tags: ["e-signature", "sign", "send", "electronic", "digital"],
