    summary: "Set up Stripe as your payment processor. Accept credit cards, debit cards, and bank transfers from clients worldwide.",
    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Settings > Payments in your dashboard.\n2. Click Connect with Stripe.\n3. You will be redirected to Stripe to create or sign in to your account.\n4. Enter your business information and verify your identity.\n5. Add your bank account for receiving payouts.\n6. Complete the Stripe onboarding process.\n7. Return to Fotiqo where your Stripe account will be connected.\n8. Process a test payment to verify everything works correctly.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Stripe supports over 135 currencies and most countries. Check stripe.com/global for availability in your region.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Is Stripe the only payment option?**\nA: Stripe is the primary payment processor. For kiosk sales, cash payments are also supported.\n\n**Q: Are there Stripe fees?**\nA: Stripe charges standard processing fees (typically 2.9% + 30 cents per transaction in the US). Fees vary by country.\n\n**Q: Can I use my existing Stripe account?**\nA: Yes, you can connect an existing Stripe account during the setup process.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How Fotiqo pricing and commission works](/help/commission-explained)\n- [How to understand your payouts](/help/payouts)\n- [How to understand your revenue dashboard](/help/revenue-dashboard)",
