    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Company Portal > Branding.\n2. Upload your venue logo in PNG format with a transparent background.\n3. Set your primary and secondary brand colors.\n4. Upload a branded email header image.\n5. Customize the gallery welcome message and footer text.\n6. Set the kiosk display theme to match your venue aesthetics.\n7. Configure branded QR code designs with your logo.\n8. Preview all branded elements and click Save.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Consistent branding across all touchpoints builds trust and makes the photo experience feel like a natural part of your venue.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Will the Fotiqo logo appear anywhere to guests?**\nA: On Enterprise plans, all Fotiqo branding is removed. Lower tiers show a small powered-by footer.\n\n**Q: Can I use different branding for different destinations?**\nA: Branding is set at the venue level. Contact support for destination-specific branding needs.\n\n**Q: What image sizes are recommended for logos?**\nA: Upload logos at 500x500px minimum in PNG format with transparent backgrounds.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to set up the company portal for your venue](/help/company-portal-setup)\n- [How to set up the kiosk POS at your venue](/help/attraction-kiosk-pos)\n- [How to apply as an attraction partner](/help/apply-attraction-partner)",
