    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Settings > Marketplace > Profile.\n2. Write a compelling bio that describes your style and experience.\n3. Upload a professional headshot as your profile photo.\n4. Select your photography specialties: wedding, portrait, event, commercial, etc.\n5. Upload 10 to 20 of your best portfolio images organized by category.\n6. Add client testimonials or reviews if available.\n7. Set your service area on the map.\n8. Publish your profile to make it visible in marketplace search.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** Profiles with professional headshots and detailed bios receive 5x more inquiries than minimal profiles.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Can I see how my profile looks to clients?**\nA: Yes, click Preview Profile to see the client-facing view of your listing.\n\n**Q: How do clients find me in the marketplace?**\nA: Clients search by location, specialty, price range, and availability. Strong profiles rank higher.\n\n**Q: Can I update my profile after publishing?**\nA: Yes, update your profile at any time. Changes are reflected immediately.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to join the Fotiqo photographer marketplace](/help/marketplace-join)\n- [How to create marketplace packages](/help/marketplace-packages)\n- [How to get more bookings from the marketplace](/help/marketplace-more-bookings)",
