    content: "## Steps\n\n1. Go to Settings > Privacy to view your privacy configuration.\n2. Review the data processing agreement that governs how client data is handled.\n3. Enable or disable optional data collection features.\n4. Configure data retention periods for client galleries and contact information.\n5. Set up automatic data deletion schedules for expired galleries.\n6. Review cookie consent settings for your website.\n7. Enable the privacy policy link on your gallery and website pages.\n8. Download a copy of all your data using the Export feature for compliance.\n\n**\u{1F4A1} Tip:** If you operate in the EU, ensure your gallery privacy policies and data retention settings comply with GDPR requirements.\n\n## FAQ\n\n**Q: Is Fotiqo GDPR compliant?**\nA: Yes, Fotiqo is fully GDPR compliant with data processing agreements, encryption, and the right to erasure.\n\n**Q: How is face recognition data handled?**\nA: Face vectors are deleted immediately after matching. No biometric data is stored permanently.\n\n**Q: Can clients request their data be deleted?**\nA: Yes, you can process data deletion requests from the client management section.\n\n## Related Articles\n- [How to delete your account](/help/delete-account)\n- [How to export your data](/help/export-data)\n- [How to use face recognition to sort photos](/help/face-recognition-galleries)",
